helpdesk-note.body: Michael, what steps did you take to assist Dr. Franzen in sharing her calendar with external users? A quick google search will give you the answer
helpdesk-note.body-html: Michael, what steps did you take to assist Dr. Franzen in sharing her calendar with external users?  A quick google search will give you the answer

helpdesk-note.body:
Hey Dr. Margaret Franzen, I believe that I have found a solution for you. If you follow these steps you should be able to share your Outlook calendar with external users. 1. Log into your MSOE email online at outlook.com/msoe.edu (It is important to do this in a browser, not in the Outlook App). 2. Once in, click on the button in the top left (sometimes top right) that looks like a set of tiles or a grid or Sudoku board. 3. Select Calendar 4. Select the calendar that you would like to share from the list on the left side of your screen 5. Near the top, you should see some menu options like New, Add calendar, Share, and Print. Select Share. 6. Select Calendar. 7. Type the email addresses of the people you would like to share the calendar with in the "Share with" field. 8. Once you have entered in all email addresses, hit "Send" near the top left of that window. 9. Celebrate success.
Please let us know if you were able to do this, or if you run into any issues with this.
Have a great day!
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hey Dr. Margaret Franzen,
I believe that I have found a solution for you. If you follow these steps you should be able to share your Outlook calendar with external users. 
1. Log into your MSOE email online at outlook.com/msoe.edu (It is important to do this in a browser, not in the Outlook App).
2. Once in, click on the button in the top left (sometimes top right) that looks like a set of tiles or a grid or Sudoku board. 
3. Select Calendar
4. Select the calendar that you would like to share from the list on the left side of your screen
5. Near the top, you should see some menu options like New, Add calendar, Share, and Print. Select Share.
6. Select Calendar.
7. Type the email addresses of the people you would like to share the calendar with in the "Share with" field.
8. Once you have entered in all email addresses, hit "Send" near the top left of that window.
9. Celebrate success. 

Please let us know if you were able to do this, or if you run into any issues with this.

Have a great day!

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi dettinger, I have tested every audio connection in the room and they are all operational. Please make sure if you are using either the HDMI or DisplayPort connection to set the playback device on your laptop to output to "Crestron" by following the steps below. Please let me know if you have anymore issues with this.
1.)After connecting HDMI/DisplayPort cable to laptop, press the windows key and type "manage audio devices" and select Manage Audio Devices
2.) Select "Crestron" device from Playback menu and click "Set Default" in the right hand corner
3.) Crestron device should now have a green check mark by it to show that it is now sending to the device
4.) Once the Crestron device is set to default the audio is now being output to the speakers in the room
Thanks, Tim Koruna
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi dettinger,

I have tested every audio connection in the room and they are all operational. Please make sure if you are using either the HDMI or DisplayPort connection to set the playback device on your laptop to output to "Crestron" by following the steps below. Please let me know if you have anymore issues with this.

1.)After connecting HDMI/DisplayPort cable to laptop, press the windows key and type "manage audio devices" and select Manage Audio Devices

2.) Select "Crestron" device from Playback menu and click "Set Default" in the right hand corner

3.) Crestron device should now have a green check mark by it to show that it is now sending to the device

4.) Once the Crestron device is set to default the audio is now being output to the speakers in the room


Thanks,
Tim Koruna

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Cathlyn Ferraro, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/4862
I talked with one of student workers and showed them how to add the printer.
The process is Open the start menu search "run" in the resulting windows type \\printers A list of network printers will appear Find CC 370 career services on he list click to install install printer If prompted click continue on the install driver option. The printer should now be installed
If you have any other question please respond to this ticket or give us a all at x7288 Have a nice day.
Thanks, MSOE Information Technology Tier 2 Staff Support Cameron Wilson 414-277-7288 helpdesk@msoe.edu

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Trend Micro Office Scan
helpdesk-ticket.description:
I keep getting pop-ups stating that Trend Micro Office Scan is out of date. I have updated what I can and still get this message.
How do I update this? Is this still something MSOE supports/requires? Otherwise, how do I get rid of the pop-up or Trend Micro itself?
Thanks.
Mitch Colton
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
I keep getting pop-ups stating that Trend Micro Office Scan is out of date.  I have updated what I can and still get this message.
 
How do I update this?
Is this still something MSOE supports/requires?
Otherwise, how do I get rid of the pop-up or Trend Micro itself?
 
Thanks.
 
Mitch Colton

helpdesk-note.body:
Tier 1 or Tier 2, since we will not be maintaining the subscription to Trend, if you see tickets like these where a student requests it, you can remove Trend for the user's laptop.
thanks
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Tier 1 or Tier 2, since we will not be maintaining the subscription to Trend, if you see tickets like these where a student requests it, you can remove Trend for the user's laptop.

thanks

helpdesk-note.body:
Hey Mitch,
First, we would like to assert that you are still protected. The popups are happening because MSOE is shifting away from Trend Micro, and there will be an update in the near future to resolve this issue. In order to stop receiving the annoying pop-ups, you need to follow these few steps:
Get to Control Panel (Windows key ---> Control Panel on the right side of the menu) Once in Control Panel, click on "System and Security" Click on "Action Center" Where you see "Virus Protection (Important) Trent Micro OfficeScan Antivirus Reports that it is out of date" click on "Turn off messages about virus protection"
These steps will stop those annoying update notifications.
Just to reiterate, you are still being protected. The pop-ups are simply a temporary annoyance.
Have a great day!
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hey Mitch,

First, we would like to assert that you are still protected. The popups are happening because MSOE is shifting away from Trend Micro, and there will be an update in the near future to resolve this issue. 
In order to stop receiving the annoying pop-ups, you need to follow these few steps:
  1. Get to Control Panel (Windows key ---> Control Panel on the right side of the menu)
  2. Once in Control Panel, click on "System and Security"
  3. Click on "Action Center"
  4. Where you see "Virus Protection (Important) Trent Micro OfficeScan Antivirus Reports that it is out of date" click on "Turn off messages about virus protection" 
These steps will stop those annoying update notifications.

Just to reiterate, you are still being protected. The pop-ups are simply a temporary annoyance. 

Have a great day!

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Wi-fi in the Tree Lounge
helpdesk-ticket.description: For the past week the Internet has been not working in the tree lounge. It will work in spurts but then it will cut out for large periods of time. it makes it difficult to do homework when you can't access the Internet. Thank you for your time.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html: For the past week the Internet has been not working in the tree lounge. It will work in spurts but then it will cut out for large periods of time. it makes it difficult to do homework when you can't access the Internet. Thank you for your time.

helpdesk-note.body: Routing to network team
helpdesk-note.body-html: Routing to network team

helpdesk-note.body: I'll head out and test the connection in the tree lounge.
helpdesk-note.body-html: I'll head out and test the connection in the tree lounge.

helpdesk-note.body:
Becca,
We get reports when a wireless AP is not accessible to the controllers, but we are not alerted if a device disconnects. We have not had any reports of the APs being disconnected from the network. We've looked at the two wireless access points in the tree lounge and don't see anything unusual with the configurations. One of the two is a brand new AP that provides 802.11 AC wireless; the same type that's used the CC Great Room to provide faster network traffic to newer devices. We've tested the throughput in the Tree Lounge and weren't able to duplicate the problem, though we did not monitor for an extended period of time. We are seeing a number of users on both APs passing normal network traffic at above average speeds.
It's possible the condition you reported is an issue with device hardware or settings, and not necessarily with the wireless. Please make sure you are connecting to MSOE wireless, as MSOE-Guest is rate-limited, and we offer no obligation of performance or speeds. We also recommend that if you have a usual spot you use in the Tree Lounge, to try a different area and see if your performance changes. The APs overlap, and you may be getting handed off from one to the other, and the transition isn't occurring gracefully. Lastly, if you can, please contact the Helpdesk when this issue is occurring, so they can get your IP address and system specs and troubleshoot while the forensic data is still available.
Thanks,
Paul Fabian
MSOE Director of IT Services
fabian@msoe.edu
(414) 277-2355

Maybe we could meet in the room, and go through this together when the room is open. It seems that more devices are trying to hijack the computers ability to choose the device that it's playing sound, so we need to go in and tell it to play on a different device. Can this email serve as initiation of a new ticket…that some known emails are not getting through? Thanks.
Margaret
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:

The calendar instructions worked. However, you have uncovered a second issue – I never received the email with the instructions. I checked my inbox, junk email box, and clutter. No instructions. Yesterday I had requested a password reset from a non-MSOE entity (actually 3 requests) – and NONE of these emails came through either.
 
 
Can this email serve as initiation of a new ticket…that some known emails are not getting through?

helpdesk-note.body:
Margret,
In an effort to block phishing attempts and email spoofing (an outside server trying to send mail as msoe.edu) we added an email rule to stop this type of traffic. However, FreshService, the hosting we use for Helpdesk wasn't listed as an allowed email host. The emails sent during this period would have been stopped by the rule. We have since corrected the issue. The duration of this issue would have been several hours overnight.
Thank you for pointing this out, you should not see this type of issue again. Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/4892

I did just try entering my msoe email address and password into Outlook and it did not connect. I suspect something has to change in the procedure for Windows 10. I go to File, Add account and get to the Auto Account Setup page. I enter hasker@msoe.edu for the email address, the correct password, and click on Next. It appears to configure correctly getting through to the “log in to server” step. I click on Finish and it tells me I must restart Outlook. When I exit Outlook from the File menu and restart it, it says “Loading Profile” for a while (5-10 minutes) and then pops up a message saying “The connection to Microsoft Exchange is unavailable. Outlook must be online or connected to complete this action.” It sounds like the left hand isn’t talking to the right, hence my question about whether there’s a tested procedure for reading email in Outlook 2010 on Windows 10.
Thanks.
Rob
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:

I’m on overload this term and too snowed under during the day to stand at the help desk for an hour. I did just try entering my msoe email address and password into Outlook and it did not connect. I suspect something has to change in the procedure for Windows 10. I go to File, Add account and get to the Auto Account Setup page. I enter hasker@msoe.edu for the email address, the correct password, and click on Next. It appears to configure correctly getting through to the “log in to server” step. I click on Finish and it tells me I must restart Outlook. When I exit Outlook from the File menu and restart it, it says “Loading Profile” for a while (5-10 minutes) and then pops up a message saying “The connection to Microsoft Exchange is unavailable. Outlook must be online or connected to complete this action.” It sounds like the left hand isn’t talking to the right, hence my question about whether there’s a tested procedure for reading email in Outlook 2010 on Windows 10.

Rob

helpdesk-ticket.description: The old transfer manual is no longer constiantly updated as we prepare to move towards the TES evaluation system. Therefore we would like a note included on this page indicating that if any course codes or titles have changed to confirm with the Registrar's Office if the transfer credit entry would still apply. We want this note because some students, mostly, new incoming students, might take a course that may be approved to transfer in as PH2010 assuming it transfers as PH2011 when this may not be the case. Please contact Stephan Thomas directly with questions. https://resources.msoe.edu/transfer/index.php

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Remote Desktop for Official MAGE Event
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hello,
I need the ability to remote desktop into a number of laptops for the MAGE LoL tournament.
I have begun my testing so that I can have a backup plan in place if necessary.
In the process of my testing, I have discovered that I, as an individual student can not remote desktop into my laptop from my desktop as planned.
I have received the message "to log onto this remote computer you must be..." See attached image.
As this is an official MAGE event, is it possible to be added to the group that has access to Remote Desktop?
If that does not work, is it possible to be given a temporary user account to use during the tournament? (and testing prior)
The remote desktop is very important as it allows me to stream multiple games during the tournament.
Thank you for the help,
Jeffrey Koehler

Thank you for the help,
Jeffrey Koehler

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi koehlere, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/4934
We would be happy to show you how to configure remote desktop on your laptop. The remote desktop group is managed locally on the machine that is being connected to, through computer management. Its just a matter of adding the user that you want to connect as to the group "remote desktop". If you where to bring the laptop in question to the helpdesk we can should you how to do this. Have a nice night
Thanks, MSOE Information Technology Tier 2 Staff Support Cameron Wilson 414-277-7288 helpdesk@msoe.edu

helpdesk-note.body:
we are going to have to add the required user to the remote desktop group on the computer Basically how to do this
start computer management local users and groups groups folder remote desktop users right click, add to group click add type name of domain user that is to connect to the machine click ok
Also check if remote desktop is correctly enabled start allow remote access to this computer Make sure that remote desktop is set to allowed for any version of remote desktop. Its the one that says less secure.
helpdesk-note.body-html:
we are going to have to add the required user to the remote desktop group on the computer
Basically how to do this

start
computer management
local users and groups
groups folder
remote desktop users
right click, add to group
click add
type name of domain user that is to connect to the machine
click ok

Also check if remote desktop is correctly enabled
start
allow remote access to this computer
Make sure that remote desktop is set to allowed for any version of remote desktop. Its the one that says less secure.

Thanks,
Steve Midthun Assoc.Director of Financial Aid MSOE- Financial Aid Office (CC431) 1025 N Broadway Milwaukee, WI 53202 midthun@msoe.edu<mailto:midthun@msoe.edu> 414-277-7224
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:

Thanks,
 
Steve Midthun
Assoc.Director of Financial Aid
MSOE- Financial Aid Office (CC431)
1025 N Broadway
Milwaukee, WI 53202
midthun@msoe.edu
414-277-7224

helpdesk-note.body:
Hey Steve,
Have you tried to map the H drive on your new computer?
Go to Computer
Click on "Map Network Drive" at the top of that window. Select Drive H, and type "\\homeshare\homedrives$\username" (insert your username) into the Folder field Select reconnect and logon Click "Finish"
Let us know if this fixes your issue.
Have a great day!
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hey Steve,

  1.  Go to Computer

  4. Select reconnect and logon
  5. Click "Finish"
Let us know if this fixes your issue.

Have a great day!

helpdesk-ticket.description: Unfortunately I do not remember the password to obtain my voicemail on my office phone. I would like to reset the password. Thanks!
helpdesk-ticket.description-html: Unfortunately I do not remember the password to obtain my voicemail on my office phone. I would like to reset the password. Thanks!

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Seandra Mitchell, Here's a quick way to reset your cisco voicemail password.
Go to ciscovoicemail.msoe.edu
Log in using your standard email credentials Click “Messaging Assistant” Mouse over the “Password” dropdown menu and choose change pin Using numbers ONLY type the password you want to use for your voice mail. It must be a minimum of 6 characters. Click save and your new voicemail password will be set instantly.
You can only change your password this way 1 time every 24 hours.
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Seandra Mitchell,

Here's a quick way to reset your cisco voicemail password. 
  1. Go to ciscovoicemail.msoe.edu
  2. Log in using your standard email credentials
  3. Click “Messaging Assistant”
  4. Mouse over the “Password” dropdown menu and choose change pin
  5. Using numbers ONLY type the password you want to use for your voice mail. It must be a minimum of 6 characters.
  6. Click save and your new voicemail password will be set instantly.
 
You can only change your password this way 1 time every 24 hours.

Scott:

Dr. Patrick J. Jung
Milwaukee School of Engineering
1025 North Broadway
Milwaukee, Wisconsin  53202-3109
Phone: 414-277-7257
Fax: 414-277-7462

From: Seidel, Scott
Sent: Wednesday, January 27, 2016 1:41 PM
To: Jung, Dr. Patrick
Subject: Greetings Sir
 
Dear Sir:

I hope your courses are going well this quarter. I just finished my fox valley course and am now going to finish your course. I was wondering if you could allow me access to Blackboard for the WW2 course for 2 days so that I can download electronic versions of the glossary, test summary sheet, study guides, etc. Having the material in electronic form will make it much easier for me to prepare my test prep material.

Thank you for all you have done,

Scott Seidel

got email from Walt -
I just took a look at the system today and would again concur with Eric’s analysis. While some parts of my.msoe.edu are extremely responsive, other parts will hang up randomly. For some students, running the graduation report or degree audits would take 10-15 seconds. For others it might be 25-30, but then the next one would go real fast.
That being said, I am seeing similar behavior out of the thick client as well, so it may not necessarily be my.msoe.edu that is the hang-up.
Walt

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Ms. Vernezze,
I know that over the past several months, Chrome has been implementing security measures that limit certain forms of media from loading. If that is what is causing this problem, I do not believe there is a solution through Chrome; I cannot access the page at all in Chrome. As expected, however, I was able to load the page through Firefox. Firefox is a very useful alternative if a page cannot load properly in Chrome. In fact, it's the recommended browser for using our Cisco Voicemail Mailbox.
This is the only solution that occurs to me at this time. However, I will communicate with my colleagues and attempt to get a second opinion. If you have any further questions, please feel free to respond.
Thank You,
Bryan Voss Tier 1 Technician, IT Help Desk (414) 277-7288

Hi Ms. Vernezze,
I have explored other solutions, and discussed this with others. Unfortunately, I can confirm that Firefox, not Chrome, is the web browser to access this website. The video portal is based on a Cisco system, like the web voicemail mailbox. Chrome and Cisco historically do not play well together. It's not possible to configure Chrome to function in this way. Thank You,
Bryan Voss Tier 1 Technician, IT Help Desk (414) 277-7288

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Calendar Notification for Old Calendar
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hello,
I am receiving calendar notifications for events that use to reside on a calendar that has since been removed. Do I need to update my Outlook data file in some way to prevent this for occurring?
-Chaning
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Hello,
 
I am receiving calendar notifications for events that use to reside on a calendar that has since been removed. Do I need to update my Outlook data file in some way to prevent this for occurring?
 
-Chaning

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Chaning Ogden, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/5082
If you open your outlook via the webmail application does the old calendar still show up? I have listed the steps to open webmail below.
1) Open a web browser such as Chrome or Firefox 2) In the URL box located at the top type outlook.com/msoe.edu 3) Log in using your MSOE email address and password. 4) In the top left there is a symbol that looks like a square composed of 9 smaller squares, click on it 5) Select Calendar
Does the old calendar show up in the list of calendars on the left side?
Thanks,
Thomas Schleich helpdesk@msoe.edu 414-277-7288

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Professor William Gonwa Community documents disappearing.
helpdesk-ticket.description: Professor Gonwa is trying to post his advising schedule for Spring 2016 on the community website. I was unable to find his document by searching even though he has submitted it. He is also trying to tag the document, but any tags he enters are immediately gone. should be something along the lines of "Gonwa Spring Quarter 2016 Advising Sign-up". Please contact Professor Gonwa so we can solve this issue quickly.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html: Professor Gonwa is trying to post his advising schedule for Spring 2016 on the community website. I was unable to find his document by searching even though he has submitted it. He is also trying to tag the document, but any tags he enters are immediately gone. should be something along the lines of "Gonwa Spring Quarter 2016 Advising Sign-up". Please contact Professor Gonwa so we can solve this issue quickly.

helpdesk-note.body:
I left a message for Professor Gonwa asking when a good time would be to come to his office and work with him on what he is experiencing.
My gut says the tagging is disappearing because he is typing the tags in and not selecting them from the pop-up that appears as you are creating tags. I have experienced this frustration myself.
As for the document not showing, I am not sure. I have checked moderation and nothing is sitting. Seeing his process may help to uncover what the issue is.
helpdesk-note.body-html:
I left a message for Professor Gonwa asking when a good time would be to come to his office and work with him on what he is experiencing.

My gut says the tagging is disappearing because he is typing the tags in and not selecting them from the pop-up that appears as you are creating tags.  I have experienced this frustration myself.

As for the document not showing, I am not sure.  I have checked moderation and nothing is sitting.  Seeing his process may help to uncover what the issue is.

helpdesk-note.body:
Spoke to Professor Gonwa. He was not having difficulty with the uploading of the schedule but rather having it be found in search. The document can be found here: https://community.msoe.edu/docs/DOC-6115
The issue was the tags not sticking. His process was typing in the words he wanted for tags and hitting Enter. Tags in the current community have to be chosen from the suggested list Jive provides as to type a word. I have entered six tags based on what Professor Gonwa suggested.
I will check the document in an hour to see if the tags are still on the document.
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Spoke to Professor Gonwa.  He was not having difficulty with the uploading of the schedule but rather having it be found in search.  The document can be found here: https://community.msoe.edu/docs/DOC-6115

 The issue was the tags not sticking.  His process was typing in the words he wanted for tags and hitting Enter.  Tags in the current community have to be chosen from the suggested list Jive provides as to type a word.  I have entered six tags based on what Professor Gonwa suggested.

I will check the document in an hour to see if the tags are still on the document.

helpdesk-note.body:
Professor Gonwa,
Per our phone conversation, I have added six tags to the document found at https://community.msoe.edu/docs/DOC-6115. I have checked the tags several times and they are still there.
When adding tags to documents, when you start to type a pop-up selection list will show. Choose the tag from the list. Choosing from the list will attach it to the document.
Please let me know if there is anything else I can be of assistance with.
Sincerely, Dana Grennier Digital Marketing
